detailedDescription.articleBody: Fidelity Investments Inc., commonly referred to as Fidelity, earlier as Fidelity Management & Research or FMR, is an American multinational financial services corporation based in Boston, Massachusetts.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Hisanobu Watanabe nicknamed "Nabe-Q", is the former baseball player who played in the Japanese professional leagues from 1984–1998. He also was manager of the Saitama Seibu Lions for most of his pitching career with the Lions.

DHL International GmbH is a German courier, parcel, and express mail service which is a division of the German logistics company Deutsche Post DHL. The company delivers over 1.3 billion parcels per year.

detailedDescription.articleBody:
Barnes & Noble, Inc., is an American bookseller. It is a Fortune 1000 company and the bookseller with the largest number of retail outlets in the United States. As of March 7, 2019, the company operates 627 retail stores in all 50 U.S. states. In August 2019, Elliott Management Corporation acquired the company.
Barnes & Noble operates mainly through its Barnes & Noble Booksellers chain of bookstores. The company's headquarters are at 122 Fifth Avenue in New York City.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: बार्न्स एंड नोबल, इंक, एक अमेरिकी पुस्तक विक्रेता है, यह एक फॉर्च्यून 1000 कंपनी है और संयुक्त राज्य अमेरिका में खुदरा दुकानों की सबसे बड़ी संख्या के साथ पुस्तक विक्रेता, 7 मार्च, 2019 तक, कंपनी सभी 50 यू में 627 खुदरा स्टोर संचालित करती है।

detailedDescription.articleBody: Elvis Aaron Presley, also known simply as Elvis, was an American singer, musician and actor. He is regarded as one of the most significant cultural icons of the 20th century and is often referred to as the "King of Rock and Roll" or simply "the King".
